The paper discusses techniques for learning the structure of Markov networks from data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new scoring function for this task, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with probabilistic modeling and inference, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing techniques and proposes a new approach, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory).
